	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-19T03:50:04">Ecofin Water &amp; Power Opportunities plc is a United Kingdom-based closed-end investment company. The Company's principal activity is portfolio investment. It specializes in the global utility, infrastructure, alternative energy and environmental sectors. The investment objective of the Company is to achieve a dividend yield on its investment portfolio and to realize long-term growth in the capital value of the portfolio. It invests primarily in the equity and equity related securities of utility and utility-related companies although it may invest to a limited extent in the debt securities of such companies. It may invest up to 15% of its gross assets in the debt instruments of such companies. It may invest up to 20% of its gross assets in unquoted companies. The Company's portfolio is diversified with respect to country, sub-sectors of the global utilities sector, regulatory regime and company size. Ecofin Limited acts as Investment Manager to the Company.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-29T07:01:10">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 September 2015, Ecofin Water &amp; Power Opportunities plc revenues decreased 73% to L32M. Net loss totaled L138.2M vs. income of L96.3M. Revenues reflect Losses on forward currency  contracts he decrease of 39% to L5.8M, Dividends decrease of 6% to L19.1M, Interest decrease of 64% to L356K. Net loss reflects Administrative fee increase of 7% to L272K (expense), Audit fees increase of 6% to L53K (expense).</Text>
